-- 
2011-06-21T17:38:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/empresas-publicas-de-medellin-to-seek-275-million-loan-abroad.html
Empresas Publicas de Medellin SA, a
Colombian regional utility company, will seek to borrow $275
million in overseas loans.  EPM, as the Medellin-based company is known, will get a $25
million five-year loan from the World Bankâ€™s International
Finance Corporation, it said in a regulatory  filing  today.  The company will seek to raise the remaining $250 million
in syndicated loans maturing in five and seven years, according
to the statement. EPM is currently holding meetings with
potential lenders in  New York , it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
